text:
Better elsewhere. 

Review: Chicken is ok. My opinion: The volume to keep the massive space reduces the quality... think fast food.  If you are looking for fried chicken (I'm a true Southerner), there are other places in town that don't taste like 90's version KFC. But we all love 80-90's kfc. The negative stars are for the service. So much attitude when we asked for a staple: napkins... that you should have dropped at the table Anyway.  Much larger problem here. Service is frustratingly bad. Lots of employees, but poor customer service. WTF?  

Bottomline: 
food: eh, nothing special; 
ambiance: loud; 
decor: unimpressive - fast food like; 
value: ok.
